Here's how to handle each scenario in MSTest:

## 1. Windows-Only Tests

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void RegistryTest()
{
    if (!OperatingSystem.IsWindows())
    {
        Assert.Inconclusive("Requires Windows.");
        return;
    }

    // ... registry code
}
```

Or in **MSTest v3+**, use dynamic skip:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void RegistryTest(TestContext testContext)
{
    testContext.SkipTest("Requires Windows.", !OperatingSystem.IsWindows());

    // ... registry code
}
```

## 2. Skip in CI (Requires Local GPU)

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[TestCategory("RequiresGPU")]
public void GpuRenderingTest(TestContext testContext)
{
    if (Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable("CI") is not null)
    {
        testContext.SkipTest("Skipped in CI — requires local GPU.");
    }

    // ... GPU test
}
```

Then in CI, you can also filter at the command line:

```bash
dotnet test --filter "TestCategory!=RequiresGPU"
```

## 3. Flaky External API — Retry

MSTest v3 has a built-in `[Retry]` attribute:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[Retry(MaxRetryCount = 3)]
public async Task WeatherApiFetchTest()
{
    var result = await _weatherClient.GetCurrentAsync("Seattle");

    Assert.IsNotNull(result);
    Assert.IsTrue(result.Temperature > -100);
}
```

## 4. Cleanup Even on Failure

Use `[TestCleanup]` — it runs **regardless** of test outcome:

```csharp
[TestClass]
public class TempFileTests
{
    private string _tempFile = null!;

    [TestInitialize]
    public void Setup()
    {
        _tempFile = Path.GetTempFileName();
    }

    [TestMethod]
    public void ProcessTempFile()
    {
        File.WriteAllText(_tempFile, "data");
        // ... assertions
    }

    [TestCleanup]
    public void Cleanup()
    {
        if (File.Exists(_tempFile))
            File.Delete(_tempFile);
    }
}
```

---

**Summary of key MSTest mechanisms:**

| Scenario | Mechanism |
|----------|-----------|
| OS-specific | `testContext.SkipTest()` or `Assert.Inconclusive()` |
| CI skip | Environment check + `[TestCategory]` for CLI filtering |
| Flaky/retry | `[Retry(MaxRetryCount = N)]` (v3+) |
| Guaranteed cleanup | `[TestCleanup]` method |

> **Note:** `testContext.SkipTest()` and `[Retry]` require **MSTest v3+** (package `MSTest` ≥ 3.x or `MSTest.TestFramework` ≥ 3.x).
